===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|木|卯|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p}} in oracle bone script and bronze inscriptions.

Later {{zh-l|*桺}} ({{Han compound|木|丣|c1=s|c2=p}}) in small seal script.

The glyph finally turned back to {{l|zh|木}} + {{l|zh|卯}} in the current form.

===Etymology===
{{zh-ref|Smith (2011)}} reconstructs *''[m-]ruʔ'', with volitional or agentic prefix *''m-'' (see {{zh-ref|Sagart, 1999}}) and root verb {{och-l|流|tr=r(j)u}} "to flow", resulting in *''m-ruu'' "(cause to flow >) pour out, empty". If unprefixed, [[柳]] means "the flowing one"; if prefixed, "the pouring one". Recall {{ncog|en|weeping willow}}.

